The R source code in this package is licensed under the MIT License.

The exact pCAT item wording and related instrument metadata are reproduced and
adapted from:

Robinson CH, Damschroder LJ. A pragmatic context assessment tool (pCAT):
using a Think Aloud method to develop an assessment of contextual barriers to
change. Implementation Science Communications. 2023;4:3.
https://doi.org/10.1186/s43058-022-00380-5

That article and its supplementary materials are available under the Creative
Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0). The package
attributes the original authors and source and identifies its derived fields,
classification rules, summaries, and visualizations as adaptations.

The updated CFIR mappings are based on:

Domlyn AM, Dodge J, Pfeiffer PN, et al. Evaluating the utility of an
abbreviated Consolidated Framework for Implementation Research (CFIR) for rapid
qualitative analysis: a suicide prevention program case study. Implementation
Science Communications. 2026;7:129.
https://doi.org/10.1186/s43058-026-00956-5

This software is an independent implementation. It is not an official product
of the original pCAT authors, the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs, the CFIR
Leadership Team, or the instrument repository.
